CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 13, 1969, pg. 17 reads: "Harriet Tubman Corner Stone Laying - One of the notable events of the summer was the laying of the corner stone for the Harriet Tubman Terrace at Collins Avenue and Station Street in East Liberty. Aided by the government, the distinguished group of women, will soon have a 56 apartment complex each consisting of three rooms and bath, for the aged and handicapped.  Shown here are members of the Guild, with Mrs. Calvin Bartlett sitting front center; on the right are members of the Prince Hall Masons who took part in the ceremonies - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of Masons wearing aprons, gloves, and suits, lined up on sidewalk and standing on raised platform, with man in middle holding cornerstone on chair, gathered for the laying of the cornerstone for the Harriet Tubman Guild Terrace Home, Collins Avenue and Station Street, East Liberty
